cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

The paper discusses architectures for pixel-level prediction problems such as edge detection, surface normal estimation, and semantic segmentation. These are all computer vision tasks, which suggests that the paper belongs to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of stratified sampling and sampled multi-scale features, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning and deep learning, indicating that the paper could also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of convolutional neural networks, which are commonly used in the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses semantic segmentation, which involves natural language processing, suggesting that it could also belong to the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category.
